  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protection and cash assistance towards winterization and shelter repair for displaced Afghan households</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, UNHCR seeks to improve the well-being of vulnerable internally displaced Afghan households through the provision of emergency assistance with cash-based support towards winterization and shelter repair. UNHCR are providing winterization and hygiene parcels to vulnerable households.  Provision of seasonal cash assistance for vulnerable families to meet their additional needs during the winter months, winterization package will include USD 265 cash for 3 months heating fuel and clothing cost, 5 blankets, 3 solar lanterns per household while some vulnerable households will be assisted with solar panel energy supply and refugee housing units. 

This project targets 61,880 affected people with its Emergency Shelter and Non-Food Items engagement.</narrative>
  </description>
